'''Sareh Bayat''' (born October 6, 1979 - [[Mashhad, Iran]]) is an [[Iranian people|Iranian]] actress, television host, and model.<ref>{{cite web|title=ساره بیات|url=http://www.sourehcinema.com/People/People.aspx?Id=138509210204/|publisher=Sureh Cinema}}</ref>

==Filmography==
*''Moghalled-e Sheitan'' (2006)
*''[[A Separation]]'' (2011)
*''Khab-zadeha'' (2013)
*''The Oblivion Season'' (2014)
*''Blue Guitar'' (2014)
*''The Second Floor Inhabitant'' (2014)
*''[[Nahid (film)|Nahid]] (2015)
*''Goodbye Long'' (2015)
*''[[Muhammad (2015 film)|Muhammad]]'' (2015)
*''We Will Not Get Used To'' (2016)
*''Lobbying'' (2016)
*''twenty-One Days Later'' (2017)
*''Yellow'' (2017)
*''Dark Room'' (2018)
*''[[Symphony No. 9 (film)|Symphony No. 9]]'' ([[2019 in film|2019]])

==Awards==
*[[Silver Bear for Best Actress]] in [[61st Berlin International Film Festival|61st]] [[Berlin Film Festival]], Shared with other actresses of ''A Separation''
*Best actress in a supporting role in 29th [[Fajr International Film Festival]] for ''A Separation'' 
*Supporting Actress of the Year in [[London Film Critics Circle Awards 2011|32nd]] [[London Critics Circle Film Awards]] for ''A Separation''
*Best Actress in [[Palm Springs International Film Festival]], 2011 for ''A Separation'' - Shared with [[Leila Hatami]] and Sarina Farhadi

